text: Hubby and  really enjoyed our stay at this newly opened hotel in Ubud. Nice atmosphere. Loved its trendy design with ethnic Balinese touches and the great attention to details. Welcomed by a friendly receptionist at the small cozy lounge, we were served cold herbal drinks and wipe towels before signing the pre-filled check-in form. Our room on the ground floor, next to the small yet inviting swimming pool, was awesome: clean-lined, artistic and spacious opening to a small open sitting verandah. The room was equipped with first class amenities and everything we needed (robes, sleepers, hair dryer, toiletries). There was a coffee machine with tasty coffee, complimentary beer in the fridge, bottled water and salak fruits for 2. The bathroom was kind of small but the rain shower worked well. The roomy work desk was handy, just wished it’s better lighted. Wifi was fast. The overall lighting created a subdued atmosphere and we had a great night sleep on the comfy bed with soft white linens. The Flatscreen TV was nice and offered various cable channels (news, entertainment, sports). The complimentary breakfast served at the hotel’s next door Full Circle restaurant and bar had enough varieties. Not only was the food and coffee tasty, the place had attractive modern interior and service was excellent. There was a spa offering 50% discount at the time, unfortunately we didn’t have time to try it. Well located in the famous Ubud area, we could walk to many places around including Ubud market, other restaurants and sacred Monkey Forest. Ubud provides so many choices to stay and we think Artotel Haniman offers a combination of attractive design, quality amenities, tasty food and coffee as well as excellent service by its friendly staff, all in all a great value for money. People with limited mobility and families with little children would be best staying on the ground floor as level 2 and 3 required taking the central stairs (a nice design feature of the hotel though).

Luc and Elliot.

Dear Paul,

Thank you very much for your candid review of your recent stay at our newly opened hotel. Your feedback is extremely valuable to us, as we strive to improve with each and every stay. I greatly appreciate your comments about the detailing aspects of the room and design as well as our service.

However, I’m deeply concerned about the incident you had to deal with regards to the transportation issue. Let me explain what we found out after we investigated the matter.

As far as local transportation is concerned, like many other hotels in Ubud, we are obliged to work with local community driver’s association whenever a request comes in to our front-desk.
